condition.narrative: A service agreement has been entered into with the CSA
An Envi & Safeguard specialist, agricultural economist and communication specialist have been appointed for the Project
Borrower has opened the Project Account
Borrower must deposit by 10/01/2005 $200,000 in Project Account
Borrower must deposit in Project Account on 1st day of each calendar quarter, with 1st deposit by 1/1/2006, amount required tomeetproject expenditures, based on forward anticipated project budget
Borrower must open & maintain an account in commercial bank on terms and conditions satisfactory to IDA
Borrower shall enable IDA to examine such reports
Borrower shall ensure that SOE are included in any audit report requested
Borrower shall furnish quarterly FMR, with 1st FMR 45 days at end of first quarter after effectiveness and thereafter by 45 daysafter each subsequent quarter in form and substance satisfactory to IDA
Borrower shall furnish to IDA not later than 6 months after end of each year (A) certified copies of the audited financialstatements and (B) auditors opinion on such statements
Borrower, UNCACEM SONADER have updated, and provided copies to IDA, their respective Financial mangt systems & PID in form andsubstance satisfactory to IDA
ESMF and PMP have been updated and disclosed in-country and at Infoshop
Project Agreements between IDA and UNCACEM & SONAADER respectively have each been authorized and executed by each agency.
Qualified auditors have been appointed by the Borrower, UNCACEM & SONADER
Subsidiary Loan Agreements (6.01 e) have each been authorized, ratified & executed by, and are legally bindind upon, the Borrower,UNCACEM and SONADER respectively
Subsidiary Loans Agreements with Borrower and UNCACEM and SONADER respectively have each been executed on behalf of the Borrowerand the agencies
The Borrower shall establish and maintain a FM system, including records and accounts and prepare financial statements inaccordance with consistently applied accounting standards
